76561198032575440,Not Recommended,320670,34431737,Posted: 23 August,all,potato,"I love Match-3 games, and I like the kind with minigames (especially hidden objects).  This one looked like one of my usual guilty pleasures: glossy album-cover art, modular frame story (collect items to free the personification of each month of the year because A Witch Did It).Sadly, I overlooked the fact that the core mechanicisn't Match-3, not as we know it.You don't shuffle or move tiles (""gems""); you just click on where you see 3 or more of them together and all the connected ones disappear.  I can't articulate why that's so much less satisfying, but it is.  I imagine that other goofy Match-3 people like myself will feel the same and want to be aware of this.Also, the hidden object minigame is just not possible in windowed mode; there's stuff that gets cropped off on the borders.  (It was awfully difficult on fullscreen, too; there's no way to adjust the resolution in-game and by that point I didn't want to bother messing with my display settings)."
